										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><a href="https://www.atfx.com.bz/en-au/live-chart/gold-price" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Gold (XAU/USD) prices</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> reached a new record high on Monday, underscoring the persistent demand for -haven assets. Despite the robust economic strength in the United States, this surge in the yellow metal, which had previously dampened hopes for an early rate cut, is a significant market trend.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-31776" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/GOLD-256.png" alt="gold chart" width="1157" height="644" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/GOLD-256.png 1157w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/GOLD-256-300x167.png 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/GOLD-256-1024x570.png 1024w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/GOLD-256-768x427.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1157px) 100vw, 1157px" /></p>
